SOS Biologiacal data visualisation: TNFalpha

#load libraries: library(dplyr) library(tidyverse) library(ggplot2) library(“data.table”) library(stringr) library(“plyr”) library(ggpubr) library(DescTools) library(MESS)

First, we import the SOS_hormones_cleaned.csv file and remove participants who do not have TNFalpha data at all 4 time points.

#import cleaned bioloigcal dataset:
setwd("~/Documents/8_Byrne_work/SOS_Bioloigical_data_cleaned")
SOS_TNFalpha <- read.csv('SOS_cytokines_cleaned.csv')
SOS_TNFalpha$SampleID <- as.character(SOS_TNFalpha$SampleID)

SOS_TNFalpha <- SOS_TNFalpha[4:8]
SOS_TNFalpha <- (SOS_TNFalpha %>% arrange(SampleID,Time))

#Remove participants who do not have all 3 timepoints:
SOS_TNFalpha_T1 = SOS_TNFalpha %>% filter(Time == "1")
SOS_TNFalpha_T2 = SOS_TNFalpha %>% filter(Time == "2")
SOS_TNFalpha_T3 = SOS_TNFalpha %>% filter(Time == "3")
SOS_TNFalpha_T4 = SOS_TNFalpha %>% filter(Time == "4")

Merge1 <-merge(SOS_TNFalpha_T1, SOS_TNFalpha_T2, by = "SampleID", all = FALSE, all.x = TRUE)
Merge2 <-merge(Merge1, SOS_TNFalpha_T3, by = "SampleID", all = FALSE, all.x = TRUE)
SOS_TNFalpha_reshaped <-merge(Merge2, SOS_TNFalpha_T4, by = "SampleID", all = FALSE, all.x = TRUE)
column names ‘Time.x’, ‘IL10_Ave.x’, ‘IL6_Ave.x’, ‘TNFalpha_Ave.x’, ‘Time.y’, ‘IL10_Ave.y’, ‘IL6_Ave.y’, ‘TNFalpha_Ave.y’ are duplicated in the result
SOS_TNFalpha_all_timepoints <- na.omit(SOS_TNFalpha_reshaped)

#Merge to now include only the people who have all 4 timepoints:
SOS_TNFalpha_final <- merge(SOS_TNFalpha, SOS_TNFalpha_all_timepoints, by = "SampleID", all = FALSE)
SOS_TNFalpha_final <- SOS_TNFalpha_final[1:5]
colnames(SOS_TNFalpha_final) <- c("SampleID", "Time","TNFalpha_Ave", "TNFalpha_log", "TNFalpha_nontran_win")
SOS_TNFalpha_final <- (SOS_TNFalpha_final %>% arrange(SampleID,Time))

#Clear variables no longer needed:
rm(SOS_TNFalpha_T1, SOS_TNFalpha_T2,SOS_TNFalpha_T3,SOS_TNFalpha_T4, Merge1, Merge2, SOS_TNFalpha_reshaped, SOS_TNFalpha_all_timepoints)

total <- unique(SOS_TNFalpha$SampleID)
total_keep <- unique(SOS_TNFalpha_final$SampleID)
perc_all_timepoints <- ((length(total_keep))/(length(total)))*100

    }

People show differing baseline levels of cortisol responding. We can calculate their relative change from baseline (Timepoint 1) at Timepoints 2,3 and 4.

rm(i, idx)

#For each subject, normalise time points 2,3 and 4, to timepoint 1.
Normalised_values <- list()
Normalise_id <- list()

for (i in as.character(SOS_TNFalpha_final$SampleID)) {
  idx <- which(SOS_TNFalpha_final$SampleID==i, arr.ind=TRUE)
  SampleID_current <- i
  baseline <- SOS_TNFalpha_final$TNFalpha_log[idx[1]]
    for (t in 1:4){
    Normalised_values[idx[t]] <- (SOS_TNFalpha_final$TNFalpha_log[idx[t]] - baseline)
    Normalise_id[idx[t]] <- SampleID_current 
    }
}

#Reformat lists into data.frames     
Normalised_values <- data.frame(Normalised_values)
Normalised_values <- t(Normalised_values)
Normalised_values <- data.frame(Normalised_values)

Normalise_id <- t(Normalise_id)
Normalise_id <- data.frame(Normalise_id)
#Merge two data.frames
Normalised_all <- cbind(Normalised_values, Normalise_id)

#Calculate the area under the curve for each responder: 
AUC_list <- list()
AUC_id <- list()

for (i in unique(SOS_TNFalpha_final$SampleID)) {
    idx <- which(SOS_TNFalpha_final$SampleID==i, arr.ind=TRUE)
    #Get participants AUC for T1-4:
    AUC_list[i] <- auc(
                SOS_TNFalpha_final$Time[idx],
                SOS_TNFalpha_final$BL_Norm_TNFalpha_log[idx],
                from = min(1, na.rm = TRUE),
                to = max(4, na.rm = TRUE),
                type = c("spline"),
                absolutearea = FALSE,
                subdivisions = 100,
                )
    #Get SampleID
    AUC_id[i] <- i
}

We can see that the greatest change in TNFalpha level occurs between T1 and T2. We are therefore interested to quantify the magnitude of this change per participant. If participant’s change is +ve (meaning an increase from T1 –> T2) = 1. If participant’s change is -ve (meaning a decrease from T1 –> T2) = 0:

T1T2_list <- list()
T1T2_id <- list()
T1T2_direction <- list()

for (i in as.character(SOS_TNFalpha_final$SampleID)){
    idx <- which(SOS_TNFalpha_final$SampleID==i, arr.ind=TRUE)
    T1T2_id[i] <-i
    T1T2_list[i] <-(SOS_TNFalpha_final$TNFalpha_log[idx[2]] - SOS_TNFalpha_final$TNFalpha_log[idx[1]])
     if (T1T2_list[i] > "0"){ 
      T1T2_direction[i] <- "1"
      } else {
      T1T2_direction[i] <- "0"
      }
    }

#Reformat lists into data.frames
